  "title": "getLocaleDateFormat",
  "contents": "\n\n<article>\n  <div class=\"page-actions\">\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/angular/angular/edit/master/packages/common/src/i18n/locale_data_api.ts?message=docs(common)%3A%20describe%20your%20change...#L228-L257\" aria-label=\"Suggest Edits\" title=\"Suggest Edits\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">mode_edit</i></a>\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/6.0.0/packages/common/src/i18n/locale_data_api.ts#L228-L257\" aria-label=\"View Source\" title=\"View Source\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">code</i></a>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"breadcrumb\">\n    <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n      {\n        \"@context\": \"http://schema.org\",\n        \"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\",\n        \"itemListElement\": [\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io//api\", \"name\": \"API\" } },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api/common\", \"name\": \"@angular/common\" } },\n          { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api/common/getLocaleDateFormat\", \"name\": \"getLocaleDateFormat\" } }\n        ]\n      }\n    </script>\n      <a href=\"/api\">API</a> / <a href=\"api/common\">@angular/common</a>\n  </div>\n  <header class=\"api-header\">\n    <h1 id=\"getlocaledateformat\">getLocaleDateFormat<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/common/getLocaleDateFormat#getlocaledateformat\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n    <label class=\"api-type-label function\">function</label>\n    \n    <label class=\"api-status-label experimental\">experimental</label>\n    \n    \n  </header>\n  <aio-toc class=\"embedded\"></aio-toc>\n\n  <div class=\"api-body\">\n    \n  <p class=\"short-description\"></p><p translation-origin=\"off\">Date format that depends on the locale.</p>\n<p></p>\n  \n  \n  \n\n  <code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\" class=\"no-box api-heading\"> <a href=\"api/common/getLocaleDateFormat\" class=\"code-anchor\">getLocaleDateFormat</a>(locale: string, width: <a href=\"api/common/FormatWidth\" class=\"code-anchor\">FormatWidth</a>): string</code-example>\n\n\n\n<h4 class=\"no-anchor\" id=\"parameters\">Parameters</h4>\n<table class=\"is-full-width list-table parameters-table function-overload-parameters\">\n  <tbody>\n  \n    <tr class=\"function-overload-parameter\">\n      <td class=\"param-name\"><a id=\"\"></a>locale</td>\n      \n      <td class=\"param-description\">\n            <p translation-origin=\"off\">Type: <code>string</code>.</p>\n      \n      </td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr class=\"function-overload-parameter\">\n      <td class=\"param-name\"><a id=\"\"></a>width</td>\n      \n      <td class=\"param-description\">\n            <p translation-origin=\"off\">Type: <code><a href=\"api/common/FormatWidth\" class=\"code-anchor\">FormatWidth</a></code>.</p>\n      \n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n\n<h4 class=\"no-anchor\" id=\"returns\">Returns</h4>\n<p translation-origin=\"off\"><code>string</code></p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n\n  \n\n<section class=\"description\">\n  <h2 id=\"description\">Description<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/common/getLocaleDateFormat#description\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n  <p translation-origin=\"off\">There are four basic date formats:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p translation-origin=\"off\"><code>full</code> should contain long-weekday (EEEE), year (y), long-month (MMMM), day (d).</p>\n<p translation-origin=\"off\">For example, English uses <code>EEEE, MMMM d, y</code>, corresponding to a date like\n\"Tuesday, September 14, 1999\".</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p translation-origin=\"off\"><code>long</code> should contain year, long-month, day.</p>\n<p translation-origin=\"off\">For example, <code>MMMM d, y</code>, corresponding to a date like \"September 14, 1999\".</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p translation-origin=\"off\"><code>medium</code> should contain year, abbreviated-month (MMM), day.</p>\n<p translation-origin=\"off\">For example, <code>MMM d, y</code>, corresponding to a date like \"Sep 14, 1999\".\nFor languages that do not use abbreviated months, use the numeric month (MM/M). For example,\n<code>y/MM/dd</code>, corresponding to a date like \"1999/09/14\".</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p translation-origin=\"off\"><code>short</code> should contain year, numeric-month (MM/M), and day.</p>\n<p translation-origin=\"off\">For example, <code>M/d/yy</code>, corresponding to a date like \"9/14/99\".</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n\n</section>\n\n\n\n  \n\n\n  </div>\n</article>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - api/common\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - /api\n - api/common\n - api/common/FormatWidth\n - api/common/getLocaleDateFormat#description\n - api/common/getLocaleDateFormat#getlocaledateformat\n - https://github.com/angular/angular/edit/master/packages/common/src/i18n/locale_data_api.ts?message=docs(common)%3A%20describe%20your%20change...#L228-L257\n - https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/6.0.0/packages/common/src/i18n/locale_data_api.ts#L228-L257\n-->"
